<%# Phase 27 follow-up (2026-05-17) — Bundles modal (formerly Collections
    modal).

    One layout-positioned <dialog> per page render (this partial is
    only emitted when at least one bundle has games — see
    `_bundles_for_shelf.html.erb`). Each bundle tile in the shelf
    points its Stimulus action at this dialog's id; on click the
    `bundles-modal-trigger` controller writes the per-bundle
    games-pane URL onto the inner Turbo Frame's `src` attribute,
    which fetches the games list and swaps it in.

    Closing semantics mirror the project's other layout modals
    (search, IGDB search, notifications):
      - Escape         — native <dialog>.
      - Click outside  — `clickOutside` action.
      - `[close]` link — `close` action on the controller.

    NO JS `confirm()` / `alert()` / `prompt()` (CLAUDE.md hard rule).
%>
<%# 2026-05-17 bug fix — `bundles-modal-reset` listens to the
    native `<dialog>` `close` event (which fires for every dismissal
    path — `[close]` button, Escape, click-outside, programmatic
    close) and tears down the per-bundle transient state (inline
    title edit mode, bound PATCH URL, title text, Turbo Frame
    contents) so the next open always starts clean. Without it the
    previous bundle's editing-mode toggle and games composite leaked
    into the next modal open. %>
<dialog id="bundles-modal"
        class="pane-dialog bundles-modal"
        data-controller="confirm-modal bundles-modal-reset"
        data-action="click->confirm-modal#clickOutside keydown->confirm-modal#keydown">
  <div class="bundles-modal-body" style="padding: 12px 16px; min-width: 480px; max-width: 900px; max-height: 80vh; overflow-y: auto;">
    <%# 2026-05-17 — Inline title edit. The modal title swaps per
        bundle on open via `bundles-modal-trigger`, which writes both
        the display text (`title` target) and the inline-edit PATCH
        URL (`urlHolder`) so this controller's `urlValue` tracks the
        currently-opened bundle. `[change]` flips to an input +
        `[update][cancel]`; Enter / click `[update]` submits, Escape
        / click `[cancel]` reverts. No page reload.

        Layout note (2026-05-17 polish): the display and editing
        states are sibling flex rows on the same parent. Toggling
        `hidden` swaps one for the other without changing the row's
        height (`min-height` on the row + identical flex alignment
        on both children), so the composite cover below the title
        does not jump when entering / exiting edit mode. %>
    <div class="bundle-modal-title-row"
         data-controller="inline-title-edit"
         data-inline-title-edit-url-value=""
         data-bundles-modal-target="urlHolder">
      <span class="bundle-modal-title-display"
            data-inline-title-edit-target="display">
        <h2 class="bundle-modal-title-text"
            style="margin: 0;"
            data-bundles-modal-target="title">bundle</h2>
        <a href="#"
           class="bracketed"
           data-action="click->inline-title-edit#edit">[<span class="bl">change</span>]</a>
      </span>
      <span class="bundle-modal-title-editing"
            data-inline-title-edit-target="editing"
            hidden>
        <input type="text"
               value=""
               class="bundle-title-input"
               data-inline-title-edit-target="input"
               data-action="keydown->inline-title-edit#handleKey">
        <span class="bundle-modal-title-actions">
          <a href="#"
             class="bracketed"
             data-action="click->inline-title-edit#save">[<span class="bl">update</span>]</a>
          <%= render(BracketedMutedLinkComponent.new(
            label: "cancel",
            href: "#",
            data: { action: "click->inline-title-edit#cancel" }
          )) %>
        </span>
      </span>
    </div>
    <%= turbo_frame_tag "bundles_modal_frame",
                        src: nil,
                        loading: "lazy",
                        data: { bundles_modal_target: "frame" } %>
    <div class="confirm-modal-actions modal-footer">
      <button type="button" class="bracketed text-muted" data-action="confirm-modal#close">[<span class="bl">close</span>]</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</dialog>
